    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan, then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-nutty-sweet-potato-and-corn-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat then peel and chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped potato</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until the potato is beginning to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-nutty-sweet-potato-and-corn-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-nutty-sweet-potato-and-corn-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potato is browned, add your<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>garam masala</strong> to the dish with your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and <strong>tomato paste</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>peanut butter</strong> and 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[750ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-nutty-sweet-potato-and-corn-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until the potato is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>oven-baked nutty sweet potato & corn curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-nutty-sweet-potato-and-corn-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 120ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [250ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked cauliflower rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-nutty-sweet-potato-and-corn-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-nutty-sweet-potato-and-corn-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>oven-baked nutty sweet potato & corn curry </strong>with the <strong>baked cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly over the curry with scissors and garnish with your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
